* Rationales for Justifying CS Education

* Labor market
	Not only do we need CSEd to train future programmers, but CS skills and knowledge are also useful for non-technical 21st century jobs
* Computational Thinking
	Computer scientists' way of thinknig, heuristics, and problem-solving strategies are universally important. These skills would transfer to other knoweldge domains and everyday problems.
* Computational Literacy
	A new set of "material, cognitive, and social elemtns that gernaete new ways of thinking and learning"
* Equity of participation
	CS kowledge will be required for the best and most creative jobs, for civic participation, and for the understanding the impact of computation on society.

The Labor Market

