Computational Literacy:

Andrea diSessa - *Changing Minds*

"Learning to use a new medium takes effort. The printing press was a huge leap in human history, but the leap did not happen until many more people became literate. A printing press is not much use unless authors known how to write and your audience knows how to read. Achieving computational literacy in socity means that people can read and write with computation, which includes an abilty to read and write computer programs".


Computational literacy is a set of material, cognitive, and social elemtns that generate a new way of knowing, thinking, learning, and representing knowledge.

Different from digital literacy or computer literacy, computational literacy changes the way we known, learn and think.

Concepts in science and mathematis can be made smipler using computational representations.

Make things such as learning:
